        <profileDesc>
            <creation/>
            <abstract>
                <p>In the land of Dabra Warq, a miraculous event unfolded during King Yoḥannǝs IV of
                    Ethiopia’s punitive expedition against King Takla Hāymānot of Goǧǧām
                    (1850–1901). As Yoḥannǝs IV’s forces ravaged Goǧǧām, they looted and destroyed
                    the monastery of Dabra Warq. However, as the soldiers attempted to plunder the
                    sacred site, they were suddenly attacked by a swarm of bees, divinely sent by
                    St. Mary supporting the devoted King Takla Hāymānot of Goǧǧām. Overwhelmed by
                    the relentless assault, the invading army suffered a humiliating defeat. </p>
                <p/>
            </abstract>
